  "response_text": "Creating a fitness and diet plan requires consideration of your individual goals, preferences, current fitness level, and any dietary restrictions. Below is a general 4-week fitness and diet plan designed for someone looking to improve overall fitness and health. Always consult a healthcare provider or a registered dietitian before starting any new diet or exercise program.\n\n### Fitness Plan\n**Frequency**: 5 days a week (3 days strength training, 2 days cardio)\n\n#### Week 1-4 Overview\n- **Day 1**: Strength Training (Upper Body)\n- **Day 2**: Cardio (Interval Training)\n- **Day 3**: Strength Training (Lower Body)\n- **Day 4**: Rest or Active Recovery\n- **Day 5**: Strength Training (Full Body)\n- **Day 6**: Cardio (Steady-State)\n- **Day 7**: Rest or Yoga/Flexibility\n\n#### Sample Workouts\n**Strength Training (Upper Body)**\n- Push-ups: 3 sets of 10-15 reps\n- Dumbbell Bench Press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n- Bent-over Rows: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n- Shoulder Press: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n- Tricep Dips: 3 sets of 10-15 reps\n\n**Cardio (Interval Training)**\n- Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light jogging\n- 30 seconds sprint, followed by 1 minute walking (repeat for 20-30 minutes)\n- Cool down: 5-10 minutes of walking\n\n**Strength Training (Lower Body)**\n- Squats: 3 sets of 10-15 reps\n- Lunges: 3 sets of 10-12 reps per leg\n- Deadlifts: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n- Calf Raises: 3 sets of 15-20 reps\n- Glute Bridges: 3 sets of 15 reps\n\n**Strength Training (Full Body)**\n- Burpees: 3 sets of 10-12 reps\n- Kettlebell Swings: 3 sets of 15 reps\n- Plank: 3 sets of 30-60 seconds\n- Mountain Climbers: 3 sets of 15-20 reps\n- Russian Twists: 3 sets of 15-20 reps per side\n\n**Cardio (Steady-State)**\n- 30-45 minutes of moderate-intensity cardio (jogging, cycling, swimming)\n\n### Diet Plan\n**Caloric Intake**: Depending on your goals (weight loss, maintenance, muscle gain). A typical range might be 1,500-2,500 calories per day. Adjust based on individual needs.\n\n#### Sample Daily Meal Plan\n**Breakfast**\n- Scrambled eggs (2-3) with spinach and tomatoes\n- 1 slice of whole-grain toast\n- 1 small fruit (banana or apple)\n\n**Snack**\n- Greek yogurt with a handful of berries\n- A sprinkle of nuts or seeds\n\n**Lunch**\n- Grilled chicken or tofu salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, and a vinaigrette\n- Quinoa or brown rice (1/2 cup)\n\n**Snack**\n- Baby carrots or celery sticks with hummus\n\n**Dinner**\n- Baked salmon or chickpeas\n- Steamed broccoli and sweet potatoes (1 cup)\n\n**Snack (if needed)**\n- A small portion of dark chocolate or a protein shake\n\n### Tips for Success\n- **Hydration**: Drink plenty of water throughout the day (at least 8 cups).\n- **Meal Prep**: Prepare meals in advance to stay on track.\n- **Sleep**: Aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep each night.\n- **Listen to Your Body**: Adjust workouts and rest as needed.\n- **Track Progress**: Keep a journal of workouts and meals to monitor progress.\n\n### Modifications\nFeel free to adjust the workouts and meals based on your preferences, allergies, and dietary restrictions. If you have specific goals (like weight loss or muscle gain), consider working with a fitness or nutrition professional for personalized guidance.",
